des in-depth accounts of how media can be harnessed to drive innovative curricular practice as well as students' evaluations of these curricular projects.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aFremdsprachendidaktik. 4aFremdsprachenerwerb. 4aMedia. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aLanguage Acquisition, Language Teaching, Foreign Language Education, Applied Linguistics, Media.1 aChan, Wai Meng, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChan, Wai Meng, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aChi, Seo Won, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChiang, Feng-Cheng, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChin, Kwee Nyet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChin, Kwee Nyet, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aChiu, Ching-Ya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChung, Shu-Chuan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarrison, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHodson, Richard J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoughton, Stephanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKawashima, Hirokatsu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoga, Yuya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKubler, Cornelius C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiu, Mei-hui, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCarty, Steve, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNagami, Masanori, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/